we're gonna cover
all these areas later.

00:05:25.133 --> 00:05:26.434
Revenue, cost...

00:05:26.434 --> 00:05:30.400
In doing your Web application,
one key problem we face,

00:05:30.400 --> 00:05:31.934
the key challenge is that,

00:05:31.934 --> 00:05:33.701
how do we get
all these customers, right?

00:05:33.701 --> 00:05:36.467
In a real
brick and mortar business,

00:05:36.467 --> 00:05:37.934
that's what you face.

00:05:37.934 --> 00:05:39.968
In a Web application
that's also the challenge

00:05:39.968 --> 00:05:41.300
that you typically face.

00:05:41.300 --> 00:05:42.501
How do we get customers?

00:05:42.501 --> 00:05:45.467
Well, imagine that we have
a lemonade stand.

00:05:45.467 --> 00:05:48.734
And if one day President Obama
shows up at your stand,

00:05:48.734 --> 00:05:51.968
you know how much traffic that's
gonna bring to your stand.

00:05:51.968 --> 00:05:54.868
All that foot traffic
would probably convert

00:05:54.868 --> 00:05:56.367
into some kind of sales.

00:05:56.367 --> 00:05:58.601
So one way to do this--
to get customers--

00:05:58.601 --> 00:06:02.467
is to take your lemonade stand
maybe to Mr. Obama.

00:06:02.467 --> 00:06:04.400
In our case, I'm gonna
touch on, you know,

00:06:04.400 --> 00:06:06.767
what is the thing
that is sort of equivalent

00:06:06.767 --> 00:06:09.400
to somebody with star power?

00:06:09.400 --> 00:06:11.434
The other disadvantage

00:06:11.434 --> 00:06:13.267
of a typical
brick and mortar business

00:06:13.267 --> 00:06:16.767
is that you have to do
the sales pitch over and over.

00:06:16.767 --> 00:06:19.400
And you also have to--
to make a real ongoing business

00:06:19.400 --> 00:06:21.234
you have to build
one stand at a time.

00:06:21.234 --> 00:06:23.234
You have one stand,
you have to keep doing it,

00:06:23.234 --> 00:06:26.267
and you'll scale it
up to 1,000 stands.

00:06:26.267 --> 00:06:28.968
You know, after all,
you have to deliver real goods.

00:06:28.968 --> 00:06:31.234
You have to sell
real lemonade.

00:06:31.234 --> 00:06:33.734
Is there a better
mouse trap out there?

00:06:33.734 --> 00:06:35.200
That's what we're
trying to propose.

00:06:35.200 --> 00:06:36.567
Social applications.

00:06:36.567 --> 00:06:39.000
Take your Web application
and move into social arena,

00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:40.834
and you have
a much better mouse trap.

00:06:40.834 --> 00:06:44.734
So here's a picture
you see...

00:06:44.734 --> 00:06:48.067
That ring of people
represents social networks.

00:06:48.067 --> 00:06:50.634
In the middle there
is the OpenSocial technology.

00:06:50.634 --> 00:06:52.868
So if you take
your Web application

00:06:52.868 --> 00:06:55.934
to a social arena
with social networks,

00:06:55.934 --> 00:06:58.567
what you gain
is millions of users,

00:06:58.567 --> 00:07:00.901
and those users,
they also have their friends,

00:07:00.901 --> 00:07:02.667
so you have the friend raft.

00:07:02.667 --> 00:07:04.367
What they'll do
for you is that

00:07:04.367 --> 00:07:07.734
they'll use the inherent
communication channels

00:07:07.734 --> 00:07:09.801
afforded by
the social networks,

00:07:09.801 --> 00:07:11.234
and inside your application,

00:07:11.234 --> 00:07:13.701
as they play and be engaged
with the application,

00:07:13.701 --> 00:07:16.767
they're gonna basically
spread the words for you.

00:07:16.767 --> 00:07:18.067
So in doing that,
you don't have to

00:07:18.067 --> 00:07:20.467
do the sales pitch yourself
over and over.

00:07:20.467 --> 00:07:23.934
And also we have open
technologies like OpenSocial

00:07:23.934 --> 00:07:26.734
that allows you
to build your application

00:07:26.734 --> 00:07:28.734
against one
social network.

00:07:28.734 --> 00:07:30.601
