00:12:03.334 --> 00:12:07.968
Let's talk about making money
with OpenSocial.

00:12:07.968 --> 00:12:11.100
So there's a bunch of different
avenues that you can take

00:12:11.100 --> 00:12:14.767
to generate revenues
from your social application.

00:12:14.767 --> 00:12:18.701
You can do advertising,
you can build a virtual economy,

00:12:18.701 --> 00:12:20.033
you can build branded apps,

00:12:20.033 --> 00:12:21.968
and then there's
a number of other techniques

00:12:21.968 --> 00:12:23.734
that I'll dive into.

00:12:23.734 --> 00:12:25.067
So let's talk
about advertising,

00:12:25.067 --> 00:12:26.801
which is probably
the best-known technique,

00:12:26.801 --> 00:12:28.334
probably
the oldest technique

00:12:28.334 --> 00:12:31.367
with making money
on social applications.

00:12:31.367 --> 00:12:35.067
So for advertising you can run
either display or text link ads

00:12:35.067 --> 00:12:39.901
and then charge for those on
a CPM basis, CPI, or CPA basis.

00:12:39.901 --> 00:12:42.501
One of the more
popular ways

00:12:42.501 --> 00:12:45.934
of making money
with social applications today

00:12:45.934 --> 00:12:49.968
is actually advertising other
peoples' social applications.

00:12:49.968 --> 00:12:53.267
And in that type of case,

00:12:53.267 --> 00:12:55.734
you tend to get paid
on a cost per install,

00:12:55.734 --> 00:12:57.934
so some other
application provider

00:12:57.934 --> 00:13:00.067
that wants to promote
their application

00:13:00.067 --> 00:13:02.200
that knows
that your user base

00:13:02.200 --> 00:13:04.601
is obviously
application users--

00:13:04.601 --> 00:13:06.567
a very nicely
targeted base--

00:13:06.567 --> 00:13:09.434
is gonna pay you on a cost
per install, and that ranges--

00:13:09.434 --> 00:13:12.367
you know, it could be
as low as 75¢

00:13:12.367 --> 00:13:16.167
all the way up to,
let's say, $2.

00:13:16.167 --> 00:13:19.267
So implementing advertising
is also the easiest thing to do

00:13:19.267 --> 00:13:23.200
in terms of generating revenue
with your social application.

00:13:23.200 --> 00:13:28.767
It's simply cutting and pasting
some JavaScript code

00:13:28.767 --> 00:13:30.133
in either case here.

00:13:30.133 --> 00:13:33.968
So pretty easy
to implement.

00:13:33.968 --> 00:13:38.767
So it's easy,
but there are challenges.

00:13:38.767 --> 00:13:40.167
Can't--if it was--

00:13:40.167 --> 00:13:45.000
And one of the challenges is
that eCPMs have been declining.

00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:47.334
That is a function
of the economy,

00:13:47.334 --> 00:13:48.801
where there's less demand,

00:13:48.801 --> 00:13:50.167
it's also
a function of supply,

00:13:50.167 --> 00:13:52.267
so there are a lot
of social applications

00:13:52.267 --> 00:13:54.934
out there right now,
a lot of inventory.

00:13:54.934 --> 00:13:58.200
So it's harder today
than it used to be

00:13:58.200 --> 00:14:00.601
to actually monetize
your application

00:14:00.601 --> 00:14:02.133
purely through advertising,

00:14:02.133 --> 00:14:04.367
and a lot of the successful
companies in this base--

00:14:04.367 --> 00:14:07.334
advertising is only
a small fraction

00:14:07.334 --> 00:14:10.367
of their total revenue.

00:14:10.367 --> 00:14:12.868
But, that said,
the key to it

00:14:12.868 --> 00:14:15.534
is to be contextually
relevant with your ads.

00:14:15.534 --> 00:14:19.868
So if you're developing
an application around music,

00:14:19.868 --> 00:14:23.167
then you should be focusing
on ads around ring tones,

00:14:23.167 --> 00:14:24.934
which tend to pay
pretty well,

00:14:24.934 --> 00:14:28.968
music downloads,
and concert tickets.

00:14:28.968 --> 00:14:32.868
All right, so let's shift to
a different way to make money,

00:14:32.868 --> 00:14:35.901
which is by creating a virtual
economy with your game,

00:14:35.901 --> 00:14:37.834
and this is
actually probably

00:14:37.834 --> 00:14:40.701
one of the hottest
areas right now.

00:14:40.701 --> 00:14:42.601
It's a space, it's about
a year and a half old,

00:14:42.601 --> 00:14:46.267
but there are companies
that are already building,

00:14:46.267 --> 00:14:48.868
rumors are, 100 million-dollar
businesses a year

00:14:48.868 --> 00:14:51.934
based on, primarily,
virtual economies.

00:14:51.934 --> 00:14:54.234
And to illustrate this,

00:14:54.234 --> 00:14:57.100
let's talk about
this Mouse Hunt app game,

00:14:57.100 --> 00:14:59.200
where your goal
is to catch mice.

00:14:59.200 --> 00:15:01.434
And you can catch mice

00:15:01.434 --> 00:15:05.267
by actually having
cheese and traps.

00:15:05.267 --> 00:15:08.467
But you got to buy the cheese
and traps to catch the mice.

00:15:08.467 --> 00:15:10.300
And you do that
through a virtual currency

00:15:10.300 --> 00:15:13.667
that they--let's just
generically call it gold.

00:15:13.667 --> 00:15:16.100
So to get gold--

00:15:16.100 --> 00:15:19.934
you can actually do things
in the game to get gold,

00:15:19.934 --> 00:15:21.400
but if you want
to go the fast way,

00:15:21.400 --> 00:15:22.567
which is what happens

00:15:22.567 --> 00:15:25.267
with a large enough
percentage of people,

00:15:25.267 --> 00:15:27.133
you can buy the gold.

00:15:27.133 --> 00:15:32.834
So buying the gold is enabled
through a payment provider.

00:15:32.834 --> 00:15:35.901
PayPal is a very common
payment provider,

00:15:35.901 --> 00:15:39.868
but there are about a dozen
that I can probably name

00:15:39.868 --> 00:15:41.200
off of the top of my head

00:15:41.200 --> 00:15:43.334
in terms of payment providers
that are out there.

00:15:43.334 --> 00:15:44.734
And in this case
they're just taking

00:15:44.734 --> 00:15:46.567
direct payments
through a credit card.

00:15:46.567 --> 00:15:48.834
There are some providers
that actually allow you

00:15:48.834 --> 00:15:53.100
to bill--to charge your users
using a mobile phone,

00:15:53.100 --> 00:15:56.234
using premium SNS,
but primarily credit card

00:15:56.234 --> 00:15:58.734
is the main form
of direct payment,

00:15:58.734 --> 00:16:01.901
and like I said,
PayPal is a big provider.

00:16:01.901 --> 00:16:04.167
And here what you're seeing
from a revenue standpoint

00:16:04.167 --> 00:16:09.767
is anywhere from $1 to $10
per daily active user.

00:16:13.234 --> 00:16:16.968
So let's say your users don't
want to pay with a credit card.

00:16:16.968 --> 00:16:19.834
Well, there are other ways that
you can actually monetize these,

00:16:19.834 --> 00:16:22.901
and using virtual currency.

00:16:22.901 --> 00:16:24.167
And this is kind of a hybrid

00:16:24.167 --> 00:16:26.834
between advertising
and direct payment.

00:16:26.834 --> 00:16:30.133
And here what you're doing
is you're actually

00:16:30.133 --> 00:16:33.300
giving gold to users
when they fill out offers.

00:16:33.300 --> 00:16:36.467
and who you're gonna get paid by
is the offer provider.

00:16:36.467 --> 00:16:39.934
So it could be like Netflix
that's actually gonna pay you--

00:16:39.934 --> 00:16:41.367
let's say--I'm just
gonna pick a number,

00:16:41.367 --> 00:16:43.100
this is not actually
a realistic number--

00:16:43.100 --> 00:16:46.601
but let's say they'll
pay you $30 for every user

00:16:46.601 --> 00:16:48.567
that you get
to fill out an offer

00:16:48.567 --> 00:16:50.801
and sign up
for a Netflix subscription.

00:16:50.801 --> 00:16:54.534
And so here
the way this works

00:16:54.534 --> 00:16:58.567
is when a user wants
to get some gold,

00:16:58.567 --> 00:17:00.501
they are presented
with a set of offers,

00:17:00.501 --> 00:17:02.767
they choose which offer
they want to pick--

00:17:02.767 --> 00:17:05.901
there are numerous providers
in the offer space--

00:17:05.901 --> 00:17:07.300
they fill out the offer,

00:17:07.300 --> 00:17:09.701
and then the offer provider
pays you,

00:17:09.701 --> 00:17:13.534
and actually you give
the user the currency.

00:17:13.534 --> 00:17:15.868
And so one company
in this space, for example,

00:17:15.868 --> 00:17:19.467
is OfferPal that provides
this type of functionality,

00:17:19.467 --> 00:17:25.467
here the average revenue
per 100 DAUs is about $7.50.

00:17:25.467 --> 00:17:30.267
So it's a pretty
lucrative area as well.

00:17:30.267 --> 00:17:32.968
Implementation is just
a little bit harder.

00:17:32.968 --> 00:17:34.701
obviously you've got
to build a whole concept

00:17:34.701 --> 00:17:37.734
of virtual currency
into your application.

00:17:37.734 --> 00:17:41.734
But to integrate
the payment providers

00:17:41.734 --> 00:17:43.234
is pretty easy.

00:17:43.234 --> 00:17:47.701
You're essentially gonna bring
an iframe into your application

00:17:47.701 --> 00:17:50.467
that's bringing in all the
offers from the offer provider,

00:17:50.467 --> 00:17:51.901
in this case OfferPal,

00:17:51.901 --> 00:17:54.133
and then you're gonna
implement on your server

00:17:54.133 --> 00:17:58.567
some code to actually
handle a callback

00:17:58.567 --> 00:18:00.567
that OfferPal
is gonna do to tell you

00:18:00.567 --> 00:18:03.567
that the transaction
was completed, who it was,

00:18:03.567 --> 00:18:06.400
and how much currency you should
be giving to that person.

00:18:06.400 --> 00:18:08.834
So pretty easy
in terms of implementation.

00:18:08.834 --> 00:18:11.367
Probably the hardest part
is to figure out

00:18:11.367 --> 00:18:15.467
how to create that
virtual economy in your game.

00:18:15.467 --> 00:18:18.868
So let's talk about
a third way to make money,

00:18:18.868 --> 00:18:21.801
which is by creating
branded applications.

00:18:21.801 --> 00:18:24.033
Now this approach
is not--

00:18:24.033 --> 00:18:27.234
We haven't seen it
as much here in the U.S.,

00:18:27.234 --> 00:18:29.167
but it's pretty popular,

00:18:29.167 --> 00:18:32.200
particularly in Europe
